# Security Rules

## Secrets

- Never hardcode API keys, passwords, tokens, or other secrets in source code
- Use environment variables or approved secret management systems
- Do not commit credentials, private keys, or secret configuration files

## Input Safety

- Validate all external input before using it
- Sanitize user-provided values before storing, rendering, or passing them to downstream systems
- Treat request bodies, query params, headers, form input, and third-party data as untrusted

## Secure Coding

- Prefer allowlists and explicit validation over loose filtering
- Avoid building SQL queries, shell commands, or HTML output directly from raw user input
- Keep authentication, authorization, and sensitive data handling explicit and reviewable

## Example

```ts
// Avoid
const apiKey = "live-secret-key";
```

```ts
// Prefer
const apiKey = process.env.API_KEY;
```

```ts
// Avoid
const search = req.query.search;
database.query(`SELECT * FROM users WHERE name = '${search}'`);
```

```ts
// Prefer
const search = SearchDto.parse(req.query).search;
database.query("SELECT * FROM users WHERE name = ?", [search]);
```
